author: Carolyn Cui
title: Myanmar to Open Yangon Stock Exchange in Early December
text:
The Yangon Stock Exchange will open in early December, according to Myanmar’s deputy finance minister, opening to foreign investors one of the world’s last untapped so-called frontier markets.
”We expect to launch in the first or second week of December,” said the minister, Maung Maung Thein, during an interview with The Wall Street Journal on Tuesday.
